    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>\({@seq1[1]@}, {@seq1[2]@}, {@seq1[3]@}, \ldots\) has \(a={@a1@}\) and \(r={@r1@}\), hence the sum is \(\dfrac{@a1@}{1-{@r1@}}={@tasum1@}\).<br></p><p>\({@seq2[1]@}, {@seq2[2]@}, {@seq2[3]@}, \ldots\) has \(a={@a2@}\) and \(r={@r2@}={@tar2@}\), hence the sum is \(\dfrac{@a2@}{1-{@tar2@}}= {@tasum2@}\).<br></p><p>\({@seq3[1]@}, {@seq3[2]@}, {@seq3[3]@}, \ldots\) has \(a={@a3@}\) and \(r={@r3@}\), and since this does not satsify \(|r|&lt;1\), the infinite sum does not exist.<br></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
